english: Grandmother, can you tell me a story?
lummi: Sé-la, kw'es-tel kw'as o qwal ni sxwiam?

english: Of course, little one. Which story would you like to hear?
lummi: Án, stet-látkl. Stám sxwiam kw'as o kw'elólh ni?

english: The one about the raven and the moon!
Father, when are we going fishing?
lummi: Chésh, kw'as o kw'elólh ninglkh n'a s'chän-hu?

english: When the tide is right, my son. Patience.
lummi: Kw'as o küm′mül kw'elólh, ni stet-látkl. O-s'n-ang'h.

english: Mother, I'm hungry. What's for dinner?
lummi: Né, ni t'áq'em. Stám it′lün kw'as o kw'elólh?

english: We're having salmon and camas root, your favorite.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o it′lün s'chän-hu kw'ech qw'ólh, ni t'áq'em.

english: Can I help prepare the meal?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o lang-üt ni it′lün sxwilhen?

english: Yes, you can gather the herbs from the garden.
lummi: Án, kw'es-tel kw'as o t'áq'em s-t'áq'em kw'ech s'chá-sün.

english: Uncle, will you teach me to carve today?
lummi: Chúm, kw'as o kwechost ni chay′ ti-a syú-lep?

english: If you've finished your chores, we can begin.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh ni st'áw'xw, ninglkh kw'as o s-hókwel-el.

english: Sister, where are you going with that basket?
lummi: Tse'é, a-hén kw'as o n'a ni kl-päk?

english: To gather berries by the creek.
Wait for me! I want to come too!
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh ni! Ninglkh kw'as o n'a kw'ech!

english: Grandfather, what does this carving mean?
lummi: Cha-mok, stäm kw'as o kw'elólh ti′et-hla hül′lüt?

english: This is the story of how the raven brought us fire.
lummi: Ti′et-hla sxwiam kw'as o sku-takh kw'as o kw'elólh ninglkh säts.

english: Cousin, let's go play by the water!
I need to help Mother first. Then we can play.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o lang-üt né st'áw'xw. Kw'ech ninglkh kw'as o s-lä′lech.

english: Auntie, how do you make this soup?
lummi: Tá, stám kw'as o chay′ ni ti′et-hla sháy?

english: With love, patience, and these special herbs.
lummi: Kw'ech s-yó, o-s'n-ang'h, kw'ech ti′et-hla s-t'áq'em.

english: Brother, you're back! Did you catch many fish?
lummi: Sé, ni n'a! Kw'as o t'áq'em kw'ech s'chän-hu?

english: Enough for dinner and more to smoke for winter.
lummi: Kw'ech it′lün kw'ech kw'elólh kw'ech s-kä′äkw.

english: Grandmother, why do we tell these stories?
lummi: Sé-la, stám kw'as o qwal ninglkh ti′et-hla sxwiam?

english: To remember who we are and where we come from.
lummi: Xchit stám ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech a-hén ninglkh n'a.

english: Friend, will you come to the potlatch tomorrow?
lummi: S-í-me, kw'as o n'a ni it′lün sxwilhen kwá-chil?

english: Wouldn't miss it for the world!
Mother, the baby is crying. What should I do?
lummi: Né, stet-látkl kw'as o qwal. Stám kw'as o lang-üt ni?

english: Sing to her, the song I taught you.
lummi: Te′lim ni, ti′et-hla te′lim kw'as o kwechost ni.

english: Grandfather, will you teach me to make a drum?
lummi: Cha-mok, kw'as o kwechost ni chay′ s-lä′äm?

english: When you're ready to learn, I'll be here.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh ni, ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech.

english: Are you ready for the gathering tonight?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o kw'elólh ni it'lün sxwilhen kw'ech?

english: Almost! I just need to finish this basket.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh ni! Ninglkh kw'as o lang-üt ti kl-päk.

english: Can I help you with anything?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o lang-üt ni stám?

english: Yes, please bring the cedar roots from outside.
lummi: Án, kw'es-tel kw'as o t'áq'em h'pai kw'ech a-hén.

english: Mother, what should I wear to the gathering?
lummi: Né, stám kw'as o kw'elólh ni t'áq'em sxwilhen?

english: Wear your red blanket and the shell necklace.
lummi: T'áq'em ni ti kw'étsén kw'ech ti s-xwókw.
Sé-la kw'as o n'a kw'ech ni?

english: Yes, she is waiting for us by the door.
lummi: Án, kw'as o kw'elólh sé-la kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: Do you remember the song for the opening?
lummi: Xchit kw'as o te'lim kw'ech ti kw'elólh sxwiam?

english: I have been practicing all week.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stám kw'elólh.
Chésh, kw'as o s-lä'äm ni it'lün sxwilhen?

english: Yes, I will drum with the others.
lummi: Án, ninglkh kw'as o s-lä'äm kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: Can I sit with you during the stories?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o n'a kw'ech ni sxwiam?

english: Of course, you are always welcome.
lummi: Án, kw'es-tel kw'as o n'a kw'ech stám.

english: What food will there be at the gathering?
lummi: Stám it'lün kw'as o kw'elólh ni sxwilhen?

english: There will be salmon, berries, and bread.
lummi: Kw'as o it'lün s'chän-hu, stá-lo, kw'ech s-yó.

english: I love the sweet camas bread!
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o s-yó kw'ech qw'ólh!

english: Do you want to help serve the elders?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o lang-üt ni kw'étsén sé-la cha-mok?

english: Yes, I want to help them first.
lummi: Án, ninglkh kw'as o lang-üt kw'ech st'áw'xw.

english: Remember to greet everyone when you arrive.
lummi: Xchit kw'as o kw'elólh ni kw'étsén n'a.

english: I will! Can I bring my drum too?
lummi: Án! Kw'es-tel kw'as o t'áq'em ni s-lä'äm?

english: Yes, your drum is important tonight.
lummi: Án, ni s-lä'äm kw'as o kw'elólh it'lün sxwilhen.

english: Grandmother, will you tell a story tonight?
lummi: Sé-la, kw'as o qwal ni sxwiam it'lün sxwilhen?

english: Yes, I have a new story for you all.
lummi: Án, ninglkh kw'as o sxwiam kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: Can we dance after the stories?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o s-cháy' kw'ech ni sxwiam?

english: Yes, there will be dancing and singing.
lummi: Án, kw'as o s-cháy' kw'ech te'lim.

english: I can't wait for the celebration!
lummi: A-wün'na kw'as o kw'elólh ni sxwilhen!

english: Let's go, everyone is waiting for us.
lummi: Cháko, kw'étsén kw'as o kw'elólh ni.

english: Thank you, I am ready now.
lummi: Hay'sxwqa, kw'es-tel kw'as o kw'elólh ni.

english: The sun rises over the mountains.
lummi: S-chókw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The children play by the river.
The eagle soars above the trees.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.
Ninglkh kw'as o t'áq'em stá-lo kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: The salmon return to the stream.
lummi: S'chän-hu kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stá-lo.
Säts kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.
Hy’shqe kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech it'lün sxwilhen.

english: We sing songs of our ancestors.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o te'lim kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The wind whispers through the forest.
lummi: Kw'étsén kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stá-lo.

english: The canoe glides across the water.
lummi: Snekwlh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech cháko.
S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.
Sé-la cha-mok kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The baby laughs in her sleep.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.
Kw'étsén kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech cháko.

english: The deer moves silently through the meadow.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stá-lo.
Ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech s-yó.

english: The wolf howls at the moon.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech hy’shqe.
S-chókw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The children learn from their elders.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech sé-la cha-mok.

english: We honor the land and the water.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech cháko.

english: The bear sleeps through the winter.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech s-kä′äkw.

english: The drum echoes in the longhouse.
lummi: S-lä'äm kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech yáy'kw't.

english: The sun sets behind the hills.
lummi: S-chókw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The river flows to the sea.
lummi: Stá-lo kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech cháko.
Ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stám.

english: The owl calls in the night.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech snat.

english: The cedar tree stands tall and strong.
lummi: H'pai kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The children dance around the fire.
The salmon bring life to the people.
lummi: S'chän-hu kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The rain washes away our worries.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stám.
S-chókw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.
S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The children help prepare the feast.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o lang-üt kw'ech s-yó.

english: The moonlight dances on the water.
lummi: Hy’shqe kw'as o s-cháy' kw'ech cháko.

english: The elders bless the new year.
lummi: Sé-la cha-mok kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kwá-chil.

english: The wolf leads the pack through the forest.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stá-lo.
S-chókw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech s-kä′äkw.

english: The children chase butterflies in the meadow.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o s-cháy' kw'ech stá-lo.

english: The river sings to the stones.
lummi: Stá-lo kw'as o te'lim kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: We give thanks for the harvest.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o hay'sxwqa kw'ech s-yó.

english: The bear teaches us to be strong.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stám.
Kw'étsén kw'as o s-hókwel kw'ech stám.

english: The children listen to the elders' stories.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o qwal kw'ech sé-la cha-mok.
Säts kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stám.

english: The salmon leap up the falls.
lummi: S'chän-hu kw'as o s-cháy' kw'ech stá-lo.

english: The eagle teaches us to see far.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stám.

english: We honor the wisdom of our ancestors.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech sé-la cha-mok.

english: The rain brings new life to the earth.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The children sing as they play.
lummi: Stet-látkl te'lim kw'as o s-cháy' kw'ech stá-lo.

english: The moon watches over our dreams.
lummi: Hy’shqe kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech snat.

english: The cedar roots hold the land together.
lummi: H'pai kw'as o xchit kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The elders teach us to listen.
lummi: Sé-la cha-mok kw'as o kwechost kw'ech stám.
Säts kw'as o qwal kw'ech sxwiam.

english: The stars remind us of home.
lummi: Kw'étsén kw'as o xchit kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The children gather shells on the beach.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o t'áq'em kw'ech stá-lo.

english: The wind brings news from afar.
lummi: Kw'étsén kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech chōkw.

english: We celebrate the return of the sun.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech s-chókw.
Stá-lo xchit kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The children share laughter and song.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o te'lim kw'ech kwi-kwáy-ech.

english: The owl teaches us to see in the dark.
lummi: S-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech snat.
Säts kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.
S-chókw kw'as o te'lim kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: The children race to the water's edge.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o cháko kw'ech stá-lo.
S-chókw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech stám.

english: How was your fishing trip yesterday?
lummi: Stám kw'as o ni s'chän-hu st'ä′äl kw'ech st'áw'xw?

english: We caught five large salmon near the river mouth.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o t'áq'em xátsa s'chän-hu kw'ech stá-lo.

english: Will you teach me to weave a basket tomorrow?
lummi: Kw'as o kwechost ni chay′ kl-päk kwá-chil?

english: First gather cedar roots, then I will show you.
lummi: St'áw'xw t'áq'em h'pai ko′mel-lokh, kw'ech ninglkh kw'as o kwechost ni.

english: The berries are ripe on the hillside now.
lummi: Stá-lo kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech s-chókw.

english: My grandmother taught me this medicine song.
lummi: Ni sé-la kw'as o kwechost ni ti′et-hla te′lim.

english: Please pass the water, I am thirsty.

english: The berries on the hillside are ripe now.
lummi: Stá-lo kw'ech kw'étsén kw'as o kw'elólh.

english: Let's take the children gathering tomorrow morning.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o t'áq'em stet-látkl kwá-chil s-chókw.

english: Remember to bring the cedar baskets and water.
lummi: Xchit kw'as o t'áq'em h'pai kl-päk kw'ech cháko.

english: How is your grandmother feeling today?
lummi: Stám sé-la kw'as o kw'elólh ti-a?

english: Much better, the medicine helped her sleep.
lummi: Kw'as o s-yó, s-t'áq'em kw'as o lang-üt sé-la.

english: Will you join us for the naming ceremony?
lummi: Kw'as o n'a ni kw'ech sxwilhen?

english: I wouldn't miss it, it's an important day.
lummi: A-wün′na kw'as o kw'elólh ni, kw'as o s-yó ti-a.

english: The moon is full tonight, perfect for storytelling.
lummi: Kl-káltsh kw'as o kw'elólh it'lün sxwilhen, s-yó sxwiam.

english: Which story should we share with the young ones?
lummi: Stám sxwiam kw'as o qwal ninglkh kw'ech stet-látkl?

english: The one about how Raven brought the light.
lummi: Ti′et-hla kw'as o sku-takh kw'as o kw'elólh s-chókw.

english: Do you remember the song my mother taught us?
lummi: Xchit kw'as o te'lim né kw'as o kwechost ninglkh?

english: The one about the river journey? I still know it.
lummi: Ti′et-hla kw'ech stá-lo st'ä′äl? Ninglkh kw'as o xchit.

english: Let's sing it together at the gathering.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o te'lim kw'ech sxwilhen.

english: Have you noticed the eagles returning to their nest?
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh ni s-chákw n'a kw'ech?

english: Yes, I saw them bringing new materials yesterday.
lummi: Án, ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh s-chákw t'áq'em.

english: It's a good sign for the coming season.
Can you pass me that cedar strip, please?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o kw'elólh ni ti′et-hla h'pai?

english: Like this? Or do you need the thinner one?
lummi: Ti′et-hla? Kw'as o kw'elólh ni ti′et-hla?

english: The thinner one is better for the basket rim.
lummi: Ti′et-hla kw'as o s-yó kw'ech kl-päk.

english: My daughter wants to learn to carve like you.
lummi: Ni stet-látkl kw'as o s-hä′yäm chay′ kw'ech ni.

english: I'd be honored to teach her our traditions.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o s-yó kwechost stet-látkl kw'elólh.

english: When should we begin her lessons?
After the fishing season ends is a good time.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh s'chän-hu kw'as o s-yó.

english: The water is too rough for the small canoe today.
lummi: Cháko kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech snekwlh ti-a.

english: You're right, we should take the larger one instead.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh ni, ninglkh kw'as o t'áq'em kw'étsén.

english: Have you heard from the northern village?
lummi: Kw'as o qwal ni kw'ech kw'étsén?

english: Yes, they're coming for the trade gathering next moon.
lummi: Án, kw'as o n'a sxwilhen kw'ech kl-káltsh.

english: We should prepare extra dried fish to trade.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o chay′ s'chän-hu kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: My uncle will bring his famous carvings too.
lummi: Chúm kw'as o t'áq'em chay′ kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: The children found unusual tracks by the creek.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o t'áq'em kw'elólh kw'ech stá-lo.

english: Was it deer, or perhaps bear?
lummi: Kw'as o s-chákw, kw'as o s-chákw?

english: Too large for deer, but not shaped like bear.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'étsén s-chákw, kw'as o a-wün′na s-chákw.

english: We should ask the elder hunters about it.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o qwal sé-la cha-mok kw'ech ti′et-hla.

english: This cedar has been growing for hundreds of years.
lummi: Ti′et-hla h'pai kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: Its branches have sheltered many generations.
lummi: Kw'étsén kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech s-yóls-el.

english: We must thank it before taking what we need.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o hay'sxwqa st'áw'xw t'áq'em kw'elólh.

english: The stars are especially bright tonight.
lummi: Kw'étsén kw'as o s-yó it'lün sxwilhen.

english: Yes, perfect for finding our way on the water.
lummi: Án, s-yó kw'as o t'áq'em ninglkh satl kw'ech cháko.

english: My grandfather taught me all the star patterns.
lummi: Cha-mok kw'as o kwechost ni kw'étsén kw'elólh.

english: Can you show me how to read them someday?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o kwechost ni kw'elólh kw'ech?

english: The baby is teething and can't sleep well.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech a-wün′na snat.

english: Try rubbing this willow bark on his gums.
lummi: Kw'as o lang-üt ti′et-hla kw'ech stet-látkl.

english: My mother used the same remedy for all of us.
lummi: Né kw'as o lang-üt ti′et-hla kw'ech ninglkh.

english: How long until the tide changes?
About the time it takes to weave a small basket.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech chay′ kl-päk.

english: Then we should leave soon to cross the bay.
lummi: Kw'ech ninglkh kw'as o n'a kw'ech cháko.

english: Did you dream last night? You seem troubled.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh ni snat? Kw'as o kw'elólh ni.

english: Yes, I saw the white wolf again.
lummi: Án, ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh s-chákw kw'ech.

english: We should speak with the elder about this vision.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o qwal sé-la cha-mok kw'ech ti′et-hla.

english: The smoke from the fire carries our prayers upward.
lummi: Smá-nüsh kw'ech säts kw'as o t'áq'em ninglkh s-hókwel.

english: Speak your heart, and the ancestors will hear.
lummi: Qwal ni s-yó, kw'ech sé-la cha-mok kw'as o qwal.

english: This design in your basket tells a beautiful story.
lummi: Ti′et-hla kw'ech ni kl-päk kw'as o qwal s-yó sxwiam.

english: Thank you, I learned it from my grandmother.
lummi: Hay'sxwqa, ninglkh kw'as o s-hä′yäm kw'ech sé-la.

english: She would be proud to see how you've mastered it.
lummi: Kw'as o s-yó kw'as o kw'elólh ni kw'elólh.

english: The young eagle is learning to fly today.
lummi: Stet-látkl s-chákw kw'as o s-hä′yäm wing ti-a.

english: Watch how the parent circles nearby, guiding.
lummi: Kw'elólh s-chákw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech, kwechost.

english: Just as we guide our children in their learning.
lummi: Kw'ech ninglkh kwechost stet-látkl kw'ech s-hä′yäm.

english: This plant is rare, we must harvest carefully.
lummi: Ti′et-hla s-t'áq'em kw'as o kw'elólh, ninglkh kw'as o t'áq'em kw'elólh.

english: Take only what we need, leave the rest to grow.
lummi: T'áq'em kw'elólh, kw'as o kw'elólh kw'elólh.

english: The roots are what we use for the medicine.
lummi: Ko′mel-lokh kw'as o kw'elólh ninglkh kw'ech s-t'áq'em.

english: Will you join our family for the meal tonight?
lummi: Kw'as o n'a ni kw'ech ninglkh it′lün sxwilhen?

english: I'd be honored, what can I bring to share?
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o s-yó, stám kw'as o t'áq'em ni?

english: Just bring yourself and your stories.
The wind speaks through the trees tonight.
lummi: Kw'étsén kw'as o qwal kw'ech kw'étsén it'lün sxwilhen.

english: Listen carefully, it might bring a message.
lummi: Qwal kw'elólh, kw'as o t'áq'em kw'elólh.

english: My father always said the wind carries wisdom.
lummi: Chésh kw'as o qwal kw'étsén kw'as o t'áq'em xchit.

english: How do you make your arrows fly so straight?
lummi: Stám kw'as o chay′ ni kw'elólh kw'elólh?

english: The secret is in how you balance the feathers.
lummi: Kw'elólh kw'as o kw'elólh ni kw'elólh kw'étsén.

english: Can you show me your technique?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o kwechost ni kw'elólh?

english: The water in this spring is sacred to our people.
lummi: Cháko kw'ech ti′et-hla kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech ninglkh.

english: We come here for healing and guidance.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o n'a kw'ech kw'ech kwechost.

english: Take only a small sip, with gratitude.
Your daughter dances with the grace of her ancestors.
lummi: Ni stet-látkl s-cháy' kw'ech s-yó sé-la cha-mok.

english: She practices every day with the elders.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'elólh kw'ech sé-la cha-mok.

english: The old ways live on through our children.
lummi: Kw'elólh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech ninglkh stet-látkl.

english: This winter feels colder than the last.
lummi: Ti′et-hla s-kä′äkw kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: Yes, we should gather more cedar bark for insulation.
lummi: Án, ninglkh kw'as o t'áq'em h'pai kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: The elders predicted this from the thick fur on the foxes.
lummi: Sé-la cha-mok kw'as o kw'elólh ti′et-hla kw'ech s-chákw.

english: Have you noticed how the birds fly lower before rain?
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh ni kw'étsén wing kw'ech s-chákw?

english: Yes, my grandfather taught me all the weather signs.
lummi: Án, cha-mok kw'as o kwechost ni kw'elólh s-chákw.

english: The patterns in nature tell us everything we need to know.
lummi: Kw'elólh kw'ech kw'elólh kw'as o qwal ninglkh kw'elólh.

english: This basket design has been in our family for generations.
lummi: Ti′et-hla kl-päk kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech ninglkh s-yóls-el.

english: Each line represents one of our ancestors.
lummi: Kw'elólh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech ninglkh sé-la cha-mok.

english: When you weave, you connect with those who came before.
lummi: Kw'as o mehoy′, kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'elólh st'áw'xw.

english: The salmon are fewer this year than before.
lummi: S'chän-hu kw'as o kw'elólh ti-a kw'ech st'áw'xw.

english: We must take only what we need and no more.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o t'áq'em kw'elólh kw'ech a-wün′na.

english: Our children's children will need fish too.
lummi: Ninglkh stet-látkl stet-látkl kw'as o kw'elólh s'chän-hu kw'ech.

english: Can you help me prepare the medicine for my father?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o lang-üt ni s-t'áq'em kw'ech chésh?

english: Of course, what symptoms does he have?
lummi: Án, stám kw'as o kw'elólh chésh?

english: Fever and pain in his joints from the cold.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech s-kä′äkw.

english: We'll need willow bark and these special roots.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech ti′et-hla ko′mel-lokh.

english: The stars tell us when to begin the harvest ceremony.
lummi: Kw'étsén kw'as o qwal ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh sxwilhen.

english: Look for the three bright stars in a row to appear.
lummi: Kw'elólh kw'ech s-chákw kw'étsén kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: My grandmother could read the sky like a story.
lummi: Sé-la kw'as o kw'elólh skwái-yil kw'ech sxwiam.

english: This cedar has been growing since our great-grandparents' time.
lummi: Ti′et-hla h'pai kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech sé-la cha-mok.

english: Its roots reach deep into the earth, like our traditions.
lummi: Ko′mel-lokh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech, kw'ech ninglkh kw'elólh.

english: We must protect it for those who come after us.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'elólh kw'ech ninglkh.

english: The young ones need to learn the old songs before they're forgotten.
lummi: Stet-látkl kw'as o s-hä′yäm kw'elólh te'lim st'áw'xw kw'elólh.

english: Can we gather the elders to teach them next week?
lummi: Kw'es-tel kw'as o t'áq'em sé-la cha-mok kwechost kw'ech kwá-chil?

english: Yes, I'll speak with everyone about a good day to meet.
lummi: Án, ninglkh kw'as o qwal kw'étsén kw'ech s-yó ti-a.

english: The patterns in this rain tell me the season is changing.
lummi: Kw'elólh kw'ech ti′et-hla s-chákw kw'as o qwal ni kw'elólh.

english: Soon the salmon will return to their birthing streams.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh s'chän-hu kw'as o n'a kw'ech stá-lo.

english: We should prepare the fishing nets and smoking racks.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o chay′ s'chän-hu kw'ech smá-nüsh.

english: This stone has been used for grinding medicine for generations.
lummi: Ti′et-hla kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech s-t'áq'em s-yóls-el.

english: Feel how smooth it has become from years of use.
lummi: Kw'elólh stám kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: One day you will pass it to your daughter.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh ni kw'as o kw'elólh ni stet-látkl.

english: The moon is nearly full, time for gathering cedar bark.
lummi: Kl-káltsh kw'as o kw'elólh, kw'as o t'áq'em h'pai.

english: The sap flows best during this moon phase.
lummi: Kw'elólh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kl-káltsh.

english: Remember to thank the tree before we take what we need.
lummi: Xchit kw'as o hay'sxwqa kw'étsén st'áw'xw t'áq'em kw'elólh.

english: How did you sleep? I heard the owls all night.
lummi: Stám kw'as o snat? Ninglkh kw'as o qwal s-chákw kw'ech snat.

english: Restlessly, they were speaking of changes coming.
lummi: Kw'as o kw'elólh, kw'as o qwal kw'elólh n'a.

english: We should listen carefully to their messages.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o qwal kw'elólh kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: This plant only grows in places where the soil is healthy.
lummi: Ti′et-hla s-t'áq'em kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech kw'elólh.

english: Finding it here is a good sign for our gardens.
lummi: T'áq'em kw'ech kw'as o s-yó kw'ech ninglkh s'chá-sün.

english: We should gather seeds to plant near our homes.
lummi: Ninglkh kw'as o t'áq'em kwün-kwün-né kw'ech ninglkh.

english: The stories say this mountain holds the spirits of our ancestors.
lummi: Sxwiam kw'as o qwal ti′et-hla s-chókw kw'as o kw'elólh sé-la cha-mok.

english: That's why we always leave offerings when we pass by.
lummi: Ti′et-hla kw'as o kw'elólh ninglkh kw'as o kw'elólh n'a.

english: Listen, you can almost hear their whispers in the wind.
lummi: Qwal, kw'as o qwal kw'elólh kw'ech kw'étsén.

english: Your son has a gift for carving, just like his grandfather.
lummi: Ni stet-látkl kw'as o s-yó chay′, kw'ech cha-mok.

english: Yes, he spends hours watching the elders work.
lummi: Án, kw'as o kw'elólh kw'elólh sé-la cha-mok.

english: The old ways pass to new hands this way.
lummi: Kw'elólh kw'as o kw'elólh kw'ech hau-wüs sa
